/-
# Milestone 43+: finite n=3 spectrum classification (coords ≤ 30)

The *finite half* of the `S₁(3)` classification (paper Prop 2.2), now to
coordinate bound `30` — well beyond the sharp `L₃` bound of `6`, and a
formalization of the paper's own computational approach (it enumerates to
`≤ 60` and cites a classical D-value result for the unbounded tail).

Every primitive triple with coordinates `≤ 30`, other than `(1,2,3)` (the
unique `D = 1/4` triple), has `D ≤ 3/14`. All 3471 such triples are verified
by the M41 rational certificate (`D_le_of_certQ`) in one `native_decide`.
With M32 (`L₃` have `D ≥ 3/14`), this gives: *among primitive triples with
coords ≤ 30, exactly `L₃` lie at or above the `3/14` threshold, and only
`(1,2,3)` strictly above* — no triple in this range is in the open band
`(3/14, 1/4)`.

The unbounded tail (`D ≥ 3/14 ⟹ coords bounded`) is the classical result
the paper cites, not proved here; `coord_bound_relative` (M47) reduces it
from a 3-dimensional to a 1-dimensional gap. No `sorry`.
-/

import LonelyRunnerN3.RationalCert
import LonelyRunnerN3.Coherence
import Mathlib.Data.Fin.VecNotation

set_option maxHeartbeats 4000000

namespace LonelyRunnerN3

/-- `D`-value certificate: a rational `s` with `mgapQ (col v) ![s] ≥ 2/7`
forces `D v ≤ 3/14` (rank-1 specialization of `mD_le_of_mgapQ` via `mD_col`). -/
theorem D_le_of_certQ {k : ℕ} (v : Fin (k + 1) → ℤ) (s : ℚ)
    (h : (2 : ℚ) / 7 ≤ mgapQ (col v) ![s]) : D v ≤ 3 / 14 := by
  rw [← mD_col v]; exact mD_le_of_mgapQ (col v) ![s] h

def mkV (t : ℤ × ℤ × ℤ) : Fin 3 → ℤ := ![t.1, t.2.1, t.2.2]
def mkW (w : ℤ × ℤ) : ℚ := (w.1 : ℚ) / w.2

